  "slug": "shared-recipe-genesees-grilled-boneless-bangus-in-pandan-leaves",
  "name": "Genesee's Grilled Boneless Bangus in Pandan Leaves",
  "recipe_type": null,
  "brief_description": "Grilled Boneless Bangus in Pandan Leaves.I gave a twist to the ordinary \u201cinihaw na bangus\u201d (grilled milkfish) by rolling it in Pandan leaves. The result was pretty amazing!",
  "cuisine": "Filipino",
  "instructions": [
    {
      "position": 1,
      "text": "Wash the deboned fish and season with a little salt &amp; pepper"
    },
    {
      "position": 2,
      "text": "Prepare the tomato, onion &amp; ginger"
    },
    {
      "position": 3,
      "text": "Mix the stuffing together and season with salt &amp; pepper to taste."
    },
    {
      "position": 4,
      "text": "Stuff the fish with the tomatoes &amp; onion mixture."
    },
    {
      "position": 5,
      "text": "Secure the fish making sure the stuffing will not fall off. You can do this by either sewing the back using a thread &amp; needle or use the Pandan leaves to secure the fish by rolling the leaf one by one until the whole fish is covered. Make sure to insert each leaf's end properly so it will not fall off."
    },
    {
      "position": 6,
      "text": "Grill it over the stove using a Teflon pan (10-15 minutes per side) or place it in the oven for 20 minutes."
    },
    {
      "position": 7,
      "text": "Once it\u2019s done, remove the Pandan leaves and serve with lime juice &amp; soy sauce mixture. Enjoy!"
    }
  ],
  "servings": 3,
